msIdentifier.repository: Kislak Center for Special Collections, Rare Books and Manuscripts

msContents.summary: Charles Rainsford's English translation of the first two books of Robert Fludd's Utriusque Cosmi Historia and other works. Includes an alphabetical index (p. iii). Several leaves have been pasted in and are now detached (p. 361-366).
msContents.textLang: English, with occasional words in Hebrew, Greek, and Latin

msItem.title: Theosophic and cabalistic tracts translated from the Latin edition /

author.name: Charles Rainsford Collection of Alchemical and Occult Manuscripts (University of Pennsylvania)

supportDesc.extent: 240 leaves : 314 x 200 (290 x 140) mm bound to 320 x 210 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Paper, 240; [xxvi], 1-11, 13-260, 262-354, 356, 356-365, [i], 366, [i], 366-395, 395, 397-449, [iv]; contemporary pagination in ink, upper outer corners.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in a cursive script in the hand of Charles Rainsford.

binding.p: Contemporary leather. Upper cover and first quire detached. Spine leather deteriorating. Moisture damage along upper portion of gutter.

origin.p: Written in England in the second half of the 18th century.

history.provenance: Formerly owned by Charles Rainsford (British army officer, fellow of the Royal Society, and alchemist); bequeathed by Rainsford to Hugh Percy, Second Duke of Northumberland.
Sold at auction at Sotheby's (London), 15 July 2014, as part of Lot 411.
Owned by the 2nd through 12th Dukes of Northumberland, ms. 600, Alnwick Castle, Northumberland, 1809-2014 (bookplate, inside upper cover; stamps throughout).
